      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Scooter Menace</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Howard N Meyer letter on menace of scooters on streets (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your Sept. 24 news article about the dangers of scooters doesn't mention the menace that irresponsible and omnipresent scooter riders are to pedestrians.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your Sept. 24 news article about the dangers of scooters doesn't mention the menace that irresponsible and omnipresent scooter riders are to pedestrians.</p>
        <p>I haven't been hit yet, but I've been subject to half a dozen near misses. I regret that there has not been enough public outcry to compel the authorities -- including a mayor's office once obsessed with punishing ''quality of life'' offenses -- to devise action to restrict -- and in the process protect -- the speed demons who drive the scooters around town.</p>
        <p>HOWARD N. MEYER  New York, Sept. 25, 2000</p>
      </block>
